To enable Wake on LAN (WOL) from the command line in Windows, you can use the following PowerShell script. This script will enable WOL for the Ethernet adapter.

```powershell
# Get the list of network adapters
$adapters = Get-NetAdapter

# Loop through each adapter
foreach ($adapter in $adapters) {
    # Check if the adapter is an Ethernet adapter
    if ($adapter.Name -like "*Ethernet*") {
        # Enable Wake on LAN for the adapter
        Enable-NetAdapterWakeOnLan -InterfaceAlias $adapter.Name -WakeOnLanEnabled $true
        Write-Host "Wake on LAN enabled for $adapter.Name"
    }
}
```

You can also use the following batch script to enable Wake on LAN for the Ethernet adapter.

```batch
@echo off

for /f "tokens=*" %%a in ('wmic nic where "AdapterTypeID = 0" get name') do (
    echo Enabling Wake on LAN for %%a
    netsh interface set interface "%%a" wakeonlan=enabled
)
```

